                                                                                                                                                                                                     Squad for Lanka tour on July 8
                      
	Mumbai: The Indian squad for the three-Test series in July-August in Sri Lanka and the 30 probables for the Champions Trophy would be picked by the national selection panel, headed by Dilip Vengsarkar, two days after the conclusion of the Asia Cup in Pakistan.         
	The selectors would choose the Test squad for Lanka and the 30 probables for Champions Trophy on July 8 in Mumbai, informed Board of Control for Cricket in Indias CAO, Prof. Ratnakar Shetty, Monday.         
	The final team for the September 11-29 Champions Trophy in Pakistan, which also hosts the Asia Cup commencing on Tuesday, has to be chosen a month before the start of the event. The three Tests against Sri Lanka are scheduled to be held at Sinhalese Sports Club in Colombo (July 23-27), Galle (July 31-August 4) and Premadasa Stadium in Colombo (August 8-12). (PTI)                                                                                                                          
